# Agent bridge (Cursor + Claude Code)

All agent context for this repo lives **in git**. Cursor Cloud clones the repo only — it does not see `~/.cursor/rules` or other machine-local user rules. This file plus `CLAUDE.md` and `.claude/skills/` are the full contract for every platform.

## Canonical docs

Edit only `CLAUDE.md`. `AGENTS.md` and `GEMINI.md` are symlinks to it.

## Skills (required)

- **Path:** `.claude/skills/<name>/SKILL.md` (also `.cursor/skills/<name>/SKILL.md` via symlink)
- **When:** If any skill description might apply (~1% chance), load and follow that skill **before** coding, planning, debugging, or opening a PR.
- **Session start** (not a subagent): Read `using-superpowers/SKILL.md`.

| Situation | Skill |
|-----------|--------|
| New dispatch / slice action | `check-slice-action` |
| New resource / tile / texture | `resource-add` |
| Phaser ↔ React mismatch | `phaser-scene-debug` |
| Bug or test failure | `systematic-debugging` |
| Feature / behavior change | `brainstorming` then `test-driven-development` |
| Multi-step implementation plan | `subagent-driven-development` |
| Before opening a PR | `pre-pr-check` |
| Claiming work is done | `verification-before-completion` |

### How to load skills

| Platform | Load skill |
|----------|------------|
| **Claude Code** | `Skill` tool (do not Read skill files) |
| **Cursor** (desktop or Cloud) | **Read** the `SKILL.md` path (no `Skill` tool) |

Tool mapping for Cursor: `.claude/skills/using-superpowers/references/cursor-tools.md`.

## Plan execution

Per `CLAUDE.md` Agent execution: for plans with independent tasks, Read `subagent-driven-development/SKILL.md` and dispatch with subagents — `Task` in Cursor, subagents in Claude Code. Do not inline large plans in the parent chat.

## Platform notes

| | Claude Code | Cursor (desktop / Cloud) |
|---|-------------|-------------------------|
| Project guide | `CLAUDE.md` | `AGENTS.md` + this rule + `CLAUDE.md` |
| Skills | `.claude/skills/` via `Skill` | Same tree via **Read** |
| Hooks | `.claude/settings.json`, `.claude/hooks/` | Not used — run `npm test` / `gh` directly |
| PRs | MCP or `gh` | `gh` CLI; merge commits; non-draft PRs; frozen PR branches |

## Subagents

If dispatched for one specific task only, skip `using-superpowers` (`<SUBAGENT-STOP>` in that skill).
